Basic Installation
==================

	First of all ensure that you have set $tpath environment variable to the MultiLanguage Transliteration directory.
	Copy the "MultiLanguage Transliteration" folder to your home directory and then set the path as below.
	if you have not set the tpath environment variable then set it by adding the following
	line in your .bash_profile

	export tpath= ~/"MultiLanguage Transliteration"

	There should not be any space between = and ~.
	
	you will have to run 'source .bash_profile' to make these changes effective.
	test that the path is set by 'env | grep tpath'

For how to use MultiLanguage Transliteration, please refer to the file README.
